devdoc.author: Crypt0zaurus https://www.linkedin.com/in/maxence-a-a82081260
devdoc.details: This contract is responsible for maintaining the whitelist of lenders, handling the creation of BikeShare contracts,  and interacting with the TwoWheels2RentLender, W2R token, and RenterWhitelist contracts.  It also manages the lender blacklist.

params._address: The address of the lender to be blacklisted.

params._TW2RL: The address of the TwoWheels2RentLender contract.
params._TW2RRenterNFT: The address of the Renter NFT contract.
params._W2R: The address of the W2R token contract.
params._vaultW2R: The address of the VaultW2R contract.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._address: The address of the lender to be removed from the blacklist.

params.name: The name of the bike.
params.registration: The registration number of the bike.
params.serial: The serial number of the bike.

params._renterWhitelist: The address of the RenterWhitelist contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.title: LenderWhitelist

addToBlacklist(address).notice: Adds a lender's address to the blacklist.

constructor.notice: Constructor that initializes the contract with the TwoWheels2RentLender, W2R token, Renter NFT contract, and VaultW2R contract addresses.

removeAddressFromWhitelist().notice: Removes a lender from the whitelist, burns their NFT, and destroys their BikeShare contract.

removeFromBlacklist(address).notice: Removes a lender's address from the blacklist.

renounceOwnership().notice: Disallows renouncing ownership of the contract.

setBikeInfoAndMint(string,string,string,.notice: Whitelists a lender, sets bike information, and mints a new NFT representing the bike.

userdoc.notice: LenderWhitelist is a contract for managing a whitelist of approved lenders for the TwoWheels2Rent platform.  It allows lenders to register their bikes, mint NFTs representing their bikes, and deploy BikeShare contracts.
